@startuml runtime_modules_component
title gpu-sim (C++ implementation) component diagram: interfaces, data flow, data structures

' PlantUML will otherwise treat this as a pure component diagram and
' reject `class` declarations used to show data contracts/types.
allowmixing

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
left to right direction

' ===== Components (code modules) =====

package "apps" {
  component "gpu-sim-cli" as CLI
}

package "runtime" {
  component "Runtime" as RT
}

package "frontend" {
  component "Parser" as Parser
  component "Binder" as Binder
}

package "instruction" {
  component "DescriptorRegistry" as Reg
  component "Expander" as Exp
}

package "simt" {
  component "SimtExecutor" as Simt
}

package "units" {
  component "ExecCore" as Exec
  component "ControlUnit" as Ctrl
  component "MemUnit" as MemU
}

package "memory" {
  component "AddrSpaceManager" as ASM
}

package "observability" {
  component "ObsControl" as Obs
  component "TraceBuffer" as Trace
  component "Counters" as Ctrs
}

package "common" {
  component "contracts" as Contracts
  component "json" as Json
}

component "File IO" as FileIO

' ===== Primary on-disk artifacts =====

artifact "PTX text\nassets/ptx/*.ptx" as PTX
artifact "Inst desc JSON\nassets/inst_desc/*.json" as DescJson
artifact "App config JSON\nassets/configs/*.json" as CfgJson
artifact "Trace JSONL\nout/trace.jsonl" as TraceOut
artifact "Stats JSON\nout/stats.json" as StatsOut

' ===== Data structures (interfaces) =====

class "AppConfig" as T_AppConfig
class "ObsConfig" as T_ObsConfig
class "SimConfig" as T_SimConfig
class "ModuleImage" as T_ModuleImage
class "KernelImage" as T_KernelImage
class "InstRecord" as T_InstRecord
class "InstDesc" as T_InstDesc
class "MicroOp" as T_MicroOp
class "WarpState" as T_WarpState
class "StepResult" as T_StepResult
class "Event" as T_Event
class "Diagnostic" as T_Diag

note as N_contracts
  Shared data contracts (include/gpusim/contracts.h):
  - InstRecord / Operand / PredGuard / InstMods
  - MicroOp / StepResult / Diagnostic
  - Event (trace record)
  PC is InstList index
end note

Contracts .. N_contracts

' ===== Data flow: process start =====

CLI --> FileIO : read configPath
FileIO --> CfgJson
CLI --> Json : parse(config JSON)
Json --> T_AppConfig
T_AppConfig --> RT : Runtime(AppConfig)

' ===== Runtime orchestration =====

CLI --> RT : run_ptx_kernel(ptxPath, instDescPath)

RT --> Parser : parse_ptx_file(path)
Parser --> FileIO : read PTX
FileIO --> PTX
Parser --> T_ModuleImage
T_ModuleImage --> Binder : bind_first_kernel(...)
Binder --> T_KernelImage

RT --> Reg : load_json_file(path)
Reg --> FileIO : read inst desc
FileIO --> DescJson
Reg --> Json : parse(desc JSON)
Json --> T_InstDesc

RT --> Simt : SimtExecutor(SimConfig, DescriptorRegistry, ObsControl&, AddrSpaceManager&)
RT --> Obs : owned instance\n(ObsConfig)
RT --> ASM : owned instance

' ===== SIMT execution data path =====

Simt --> T_KernelImage : run(kernel)
Simt --> Reg : lookup(InstRecord)
Reg --> T_InstDesc
Simt --> Exp : expand(InstRecord, InstDesc, warp_size)
Exp --> T_MicroOp
Simt --> Exec : step(MicroOp, WarpState, ObsControl)
Simt --> Ctrl : step(MicroOp, WarpState, ObsControl)
Simt --> MemU : step(MicroOp, WarpState, ObsControl)\n(uses AddrSpaceManager)
MemU --> ASM

Simt --> Obs : emit(Event)\n+ counter(key)
Obs --> Trace : push/snapshot
Obs --> Ctrs : inc/snapshot
Obs --> T_Event
Obs --> T_Diag

' ===== Outputs =====

CLI --> Obs : trace_snapshot()\n+ counters_snapshot()
CLI --> FileIO : write trace/stats
FileIO --> TraceOut
FileIO --> StatsOut

note right of CLI
  Trace format: JSON lines\n(event_to_json_line)
  Stats format: JSON\n(stats_to_json)
end note

' ===== Type ownership / containment highlights =====

RT ..> T_AppConfig : stores
RT ..> Obs : owns
RT ..> ASM : owns

Obs ..> Trace : contains
Obs ..> Ctrs : contains

T_KernelImage ..> T_InstRecord : insts[*]
T_ModuleImage ..> T_KernelImage : kernels[*]
T_InstDesc ..> T_MicroOp : uops[*] (template)
Simt ..> T_WarpState : local state

legend left
  Focus:
  - Module boundaries are code directories under src/ and public headers under include/.
  - Arrows label runtime data interfaces (types or file artifacts).
endlegend

@enduml
